Slice onions. Heat oil in saucepan and stir in onions. Caramelize, uncovered, on low heat for 25 minutes, until golden brown, stirring often. Stir in sugar and flour and cook for 2 minutes. Prepare a large saucepan with the broth, wine, bay leaf, basil, nutmeg, salt and pepper. Simmer for 20 minutes, covered. Add the onion mixture to the broth mixture and stir. Dry bread in oven at 325 degrees F for about 20 minutes. Grate mozzarella and parmesan cheese. Pour soup into individual ovenproof bowls. Top each with bread slice. Sprinkle with variety of cheeses. Bake at 350 degrees F about 15 minutes, then lightly broil to brown cheese. Serve.